                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1411: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. I have informed Ocheltree of the contents of the Department’s telegram No.
                    23, March 25, midnight [<hi rend="italic">noon</hi>], and asked him to sound out
                    Licenciado Zúñiga Montúfar regarding an early visit with me to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
